There was a larger yarding of 84 cattle at Powranna on Tuesday with more cows included. The trade yearlings met a stronger market with steers making 250c to 272c and heifers 244c to 260c/kg.
The few grown steers made 204c to 248c while heavy beef cows made 184c to 200c and the seconds 120c to 170c/kg liveweight.

Market Reporter Richard Bailey
